Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.33,0:01:57.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So how has living here been?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.46,0:02:00.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is a wonderful House.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.13,0:02:02.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All the children are smart and well-behaved.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.93,0:02:07.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Lately you've been following\Ninstructions and being well-behaved as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.47,0:02:10.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.06,0:02:15.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You try to get along with the children,\Nand play tag with all your strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.90,0:02:20.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried because you were a tomboy,\Nbut it looks like you're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.28,0:02:22.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.07,0:02:28.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Insurance that I called for, just in case,\Nto make sure the products are protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.83,0:02:34.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you don't need to know\Nwhich one knows the secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.75,0:02:37.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and just pretend to be obedient, work hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.75,0:02:42.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and laugh that you've grasped\Nsome sort of weakness over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.21,0:02:43.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't think of...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.05,0:02:48.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have nothing else to do\Nthan be my pawn, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:53.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you behave...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.06,0:03:01.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure that you become a Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.19,0:03:02.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.99,0:03:09.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're a smart girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.49,0:03:11.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make any more mistakes from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.70,0:03:49.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.12,0:03:54.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just you watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.20,0:03:58.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll drag you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:09.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.80,0:04:12.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will be Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.85,0:04:17.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.48,0:04:20.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Starting today, let's play tag in teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.90,0:04:22.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In teams?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.11,0:04:25.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, most of them would die\Nif they escaped individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:26.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:29.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But everyone's movements aren't bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.74,0:04:31.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we shouldn't break them up individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.99,0:04:34.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll make formations and run away in teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.74,0:04:37.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll play tag in a way that's similar\Nto what the real escape would be like.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.79,0:04:38.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The real escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.91,0:04:40.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I have another idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.54,0:04:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's tell Don and Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.67,0:04:46.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll explain the situation\Nand have them lead the teams.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.01,0:04:49.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What if they're Mom's informant?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:54.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No worries. Finding out who the informant is,\Nand also winning them over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.81,0:04:56.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can do them simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.31,0:04:59.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I've already made arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.27,0:05:01.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.73,0:05:05.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For now, I'll tell you 100 types\Nof formation patterns, so memorize them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.23,0:05:07.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean by ear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.11,0:05:09.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.03,0:05:12.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Easy peasy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.95,0:05:18.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- I won't get caught this time!\N- Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.45,0:05:21.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, try not to get caught for 10 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.17,0:05:23.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Start.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.05,0:05:27.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:30.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's succeed and surprise Ray!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.76,0:05:32.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.93,0:06:16.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.60,0:06:18.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Phil, you were good at running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.27,0:06:20.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is really fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.98,0:06:22.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be leader for the next one!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.85,0:06:25.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But let's take a break for a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.23,0:06:32.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like playing tag\Nin teams is going to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.74,0:06:36.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was Phil's score again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.87,0:06:40.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.83,0:06:44.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's averaging about 203 lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.42,0:06:45.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's high.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:51.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He was one of the last ones remaining this time\Nand also when we played tag with Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.13,0:06:57.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He's always looking for you and Norman\Nwith Sherry, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.68,0:07:06.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!\NI don't want to suspect anyone after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.52,0:07:09.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. Even if you don't want to,\Nyou need to be more suspicious! Thoroughly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.07,0:07:11.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}This is life or death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.37,0:07:24.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:27.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Any progress on how\Nto break the tracking devices?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.96,0:07:29.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long do you need until you're prepared?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.21,0:07:31.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.92,0:07:32.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.17,0:07:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's commence the plan\Nten days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:39.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll carry out the escape plan\Nten days from now, on November 8th.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.22,0:07:43.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.39,0:07:45.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it too soon? I mean, it's fine, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.60,0:07:47.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.06,0:07:49.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been two weeks since Conny was shipped.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:53.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The shipment cycle is at least two months,\Nso we should have about a month and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:57.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought the plan was to carefully prepare\Nduring that time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.36,0:08:03.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Just as you thought that way,\NMom's controlling us to think that way, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.74,0:08:05.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So we need to outwit that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.21,0:08:09.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And if we fail from being too rushed?\NThen what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:12.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, we need to escape\Nbefore winter comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.21,0:08:17.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as we break the tracking devices,\Nlet's execute our escape plan as quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.26,0:08:20.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That means we have to do what's necessary\Nin the remaining ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:27.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk to Don and Gilda tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.16,0:09:23.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Both of you, follow my lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:30.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.04,0:09:34.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.84,0:09:37.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Human trafficking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:46.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. All of our siblings\Nhave been sold off to bad people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.69,0:09:55.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way! No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.19,0:10:01.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the walls, the gate, and the siblings\Nwho left and never write us letters...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:02.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh come on, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.61,0:10:06.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So what's the punch line?\NWhat kind of prank is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.25,0:10:14.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're not saying it's true, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.54,0:10:15.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.21,0:10:19.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Then what about Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.17,0:10:21.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She's the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.88,0:10:24.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,who's selling us to bad people.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.93,0:10:28.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way that kind Mom\Nwould do such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.47,0:10:29.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take it back, Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.14,0:10:31.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:37.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma loves this House and Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.73,0:10:39.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So there's no way she would lie about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.36,0:10:43.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.03,0:10:47.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I did think it was weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.03,0:10:50.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The night Conny left...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.87,0:10:53.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma and Norman went to the gate, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.62,0:10:54.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.42,0:10:59.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you broke the rules,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.25,0:11:04.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,both of you would usually apologize immediately,\Nand everything would be back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.05,0:11:05.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you haven't done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.39,0:11:11.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, you've become so serious now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.68,0:11:14.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I couldn't ask about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.15,0:11:23.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.11,0:11:24.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I made you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:27.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see it, Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.99,0:11:30.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Conny being sold off...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.45,0:11:32.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to those bad people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:35.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:37.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But we didn't make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.67,0:11:40.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Conny is safe, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.09,0:11:41.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:45.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But how...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.72,0:11:47.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How could this even happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.93,0:11:50.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if this proves anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.18,0:11:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but these are our siblings' scores that I had\NRay and Emma look into for the past few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:11:57.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Scores?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.48,0:12:05.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The ones who left are over six years old\Nand adopted in the order of lowest scores first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.36,0:12:06.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that weird?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:09.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True, Conny's scores are...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.32,0:12:10.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And Hao and Sadie...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.28,0:12:13.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:15.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don. Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.83,0:12:19.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's escape from here\Nand go help Conny and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.42,0:12:21.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all run away from here, together!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.46,0:12:23.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:43.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Norman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.61,0:12:45.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this about the shipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.11,0:12:46.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean you "don't know"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.11,0:12:49.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should have said they died!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.03,0:12:52.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was the best way\Nto smoothly get them to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.16,0:12:54.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If they weren't the spies after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.20,0:12:57.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then this kind of lie is too cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.41,0:13:00.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"They're alive"?\NDon't give them hope that doesn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.38,0:13:05.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How and when are you going\Nto tell them the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.55,0:13:06.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell them?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.96,0:13:09.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll cross that bridge when I get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.30,0:13:13.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're still assuming they might be the spies, too.\NSo I'm going to lay a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.89,0:13:14.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.64,0:13:18.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell both of them where the rope is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.35,0:13:22.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell Don it's under my bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.73,0:13:25.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To Gilda, I'll tell her it's in the ceiling\Nof the second floor bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.73,0:13:31.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who will make a move?\NHow will Mom find out? We can trace it from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.78,0:13:37.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And the ropes? If they weren't the spies,\Nand there's nothing there, it'll get complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:39.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have something else for that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.50,0:13:42.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're completely prepared, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.63,0:13:43.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.38,0:13:45.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have to outwit her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.01,0:13:51.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.47,0:13:57.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since we talked like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.64,0:14:00.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's weird, right?\NEven though we're together every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.40,0:14:06.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And we'll be together from now on, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.57,0:14:12.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.93,0:15:21.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.22,0:15:24.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The rope is hidden in Norman's bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.32,0:15:34.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been waiting for you, Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.97,0:15:57.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, please talk to me, Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.39,0:16:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About that issue, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:16.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't anything I'm worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.57,0:16:20.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate that you frequently\Nchecked on me out of concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.16,0:16:24.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.29,0:16:26.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm okay now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.37,0:16:28.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you can leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:29.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.25,0:16:36.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Emma told you everything, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.10,0:16:46.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gilda, so you know about\Neverything now, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.86,0:16:56.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Darn, it's too bad, Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.19,0:16:59.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we could become friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:03.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So who else knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.41,0:17:07.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Norman. Ray. And?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.33,0:17:14.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let only you go,\Nso why don't we join hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.68,0:17:25.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.39,0:17:30.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.69,0:17:35.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I just had a fight with Emma.\NBut we made up, so everything's okay now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.19,0:17:41.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So it was my misunderstanding.\NI apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.03,0:17:50.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you think Emma has lied to you,\Ncome back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:54.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you later, Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.55,0:18:06.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:07.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gilda.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.15,0:18:20.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not giving up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.40,0:18:23.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I can't get Gilda...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.41,0:18:28.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The great Thoma has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.62,0:18:32.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it's okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.79,0:18:35.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. Mom's watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.63,0:18:44.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,According to what Emma told me,\NGilda is innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.26,0:18:49.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ray. I wonder why\Ntraitors betray others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.68,0:18:52.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's because there must be\Nsome merit in doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.89,0:18:56.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For example, they can be spared from\Nbeing shipped out and can become an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.48,0:19:01.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A guarantee to live, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.16,0:19:11.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see, so this was training for running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.08,0:19:18.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.63,0:19:19.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Three...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.46,0:19:20.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.42,0:19:22.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can I talk to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.92,0:19:25.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to hear your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.97,0:19:30.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What if there's someone who is willingly\Nbeing an agent of the demons,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.93,0:19:35.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and that by spying on us,\Nthey are guaranteed to continue living...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.56,0:19:39.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You mean, in exchange for spying on us,\Nthey won't get shipped out and can live?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.90,0:19:43.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Would you leave that person behind?\NOr take them with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.07,0:19:47.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd take them with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.74,0:19:50.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that person didn't want that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.99,0:19:52.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'd force them to come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.12,0:19:57.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Because if we escape, that person's life\Nmight not be guaranteed anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.63,0:20:03.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I want to believe, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.59,0:20:06.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The incident with Gilda made me realize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.97,0:20:11.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ray told me to suspect everyone, but even\Nif there's a traitor who is a demon's agent,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.97,0:20:14.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,no one within our siblings is a bad person.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:17.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're family that grew up together.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.60,0:20:20.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that person gets in the way,\Nbetrays us, or says I'm naïve,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.98,0:20:22.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to believe in that person!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.78,0:20:28.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you would say that, Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:20:58.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.65,0:21:02.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.98,0:21:04.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.94,0:21:08.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's confirmed that it's Don.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.95,0:21:09.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.91,0:21:17.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So you're the traitor, Ray.
